<graph edgedefault="undirected"><node id="&quot;ELTON&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Elton is a naturalist who introduced a novel, functional approach to understanding communities, focusing on food chains and food cycles."&lt;SEP&gt;"Elton is a person who, despite the failure to explore Itsbergen, found a book on Norwegian mammals during a stopover at Tromsø."&lt;SEP&gt;"Elton was sometimes a tent-mate of Howard Florey during the 1924 expedition."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-2cf75178f08ca72e7e7d6a42f92d57fb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0c9f93f77f118c5c6b3d89cffbdd6bcc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-765643b040c7183f699bffd06fee52b2</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 18}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 87}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ARCTIC ISLANDS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Arctic Islands are the geographical setting where Elton studied the food economy and relationships among creatures."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0c9f93f77f118c5c6b3d89cffbdd6bcc</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 18}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 87}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FOOD&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Food is a precious commodity in the Arctic islands, crucial for sustaining life and forming the basis of food chains and food cycles."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0c9f93f77f118c5c6b3d89cffbdd6bcc</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 18}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 87}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MARINE ANIMALS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Marine Animals include plankton and fish, which form the base of the food chain by being consumed by seabirds and seals."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0c9f93f77f118c5c6b3d89cffbdd6bcc</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 18}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 87}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SEABIRDS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Seabirds are part of the food chain, consuming marine animals and being preyed upon by arctic foxes and certain gulls."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0c9f93f77f118c5c6b3d89cffbdd6bcc</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 18}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 87}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SEALS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Seals are part of the food chain, being consumed by polar bears and also by seabirds."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0c9f93f77f118c5c6b3d89cffbdd6bcc</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 18}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 87}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ARCTIC FOX&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Arctic Fox is a predator in the food chain, consuming seabirds and seals."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Arctic Fox is part of the food chain on Bear Island, representing a higher trophic level in the ecosystem."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0c9f93f77f118c5c6b3d89cffbdd6bcc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1bcf9db76c14967fea58e57752fcd527</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 18}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 85}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;POLAR BEARS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Polar Bears are at the top of the food chain, consuming seals."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0c9f93f77f118c5c6b3d89cffbdd6bcc</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 18}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 87}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SKUA&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Skua is a bird that preys on seabirds."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0c9f93f77f118c5c6b3d89cffbdd6bcc</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 18}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 87}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GLAUCOUS GULL&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Glaucous Gull is another bird that preys on seabirds."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0c9f93f77f118c5c6b3d89cffbdd6bcc</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 18}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 87}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PLANTS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Plants are nourished by nitrogen from seabird droppings, forming part of the food cycle."&lt;SEP&gt;"Plants are organisms that consume nutrients from bacteria and produce food for insects."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0c9f93f77f118c5c6b3d89cffbdd6bcc</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 18}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 87}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;INSECTS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Insects are organisms that consume plants and are part of the food cycle."&lt;SEP&gt;"Insects consume plants and are part of the food cycle, being preyed upon by land birds."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0c9f93f77f118c5c6b3d89cffbdd6bcc</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 18}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 87}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LAND BIRDS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Land Birds are organisms that consume insects and are part of the food cycle."&lt;SEP&gt;"Land Birds such as ptarmigan and sandpiper consume insects and are preyed upon by arctic foxes."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0c9f93f77f118c5c6b3d89cffbdd6bcc</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 18}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 87}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BACTERIA&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Bacteria are microorganisms that Monod studied in his research."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bacteria are microorganisms that use nitrogen from seabird droppings to produce food for plants."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bacteria use nitrogen from seabird droppings to produce food for plants, forming part of the food cycle."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0c9f93f77f118c5c6b3d89cffbdd6bcc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-765643b040c7183f699bffd06fee52b2</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 18}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 83}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 135}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FOOD CHAINS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Food Chains are the linear relationships among organisms based on food consumption, as defined by Elton."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0c9f93f77f118c5c6b3d89cffbdd6bcc</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 18}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 87}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FOOD CYCLES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Food Cycles are the interconnected networks of food chains, as defined by Elton, later called food webs."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0c9f93f77f118c5c6b3d89cffbdd6bcc</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 18}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 87}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FOOD WEBS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Food Webs are the complex interconnections of food chains, as defined by Elton, representing the full ecosystem."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0c9f93f77f118c5c6b3d89cffbdd6bcc</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 18}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 87}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BEAR ISLAND&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Bear Island is a location where the first food web was drawn, specifically mentioned in relation to the food chain schematic."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bear Island is the specific location where Elton conducted his research on food chains and food cycles."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0c9f93f77f118c5c6b3d89cffbdd6bcc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1bcf9db76c14967fea58e57752fcd527</data>
