</node>
<node id="&quot;DANCE LANGUAGE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Dance Language refers to a form of communication used by bees, which involves specific movements to convey information to other bees within the colony."&lt;SEP&gt;"Dance language is a form of communication used by bees to convey specific information about food sources and other important locations."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-92d1ecd04d2635b88e1772df1127a05d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f2152717d29b2ba8bf6420f9378fb63a</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 64}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 128}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NECTAR&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Nectar is a sweet liquid produced by plants that bees collect as a food source."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f2152717d29b2ba8bf6420f9378fb63a</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 63}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;POLLEN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Pollen is a fine powder produced by plants that bees collect as a food source and use for reproduction."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f2152717d29b2ba8bf6420f9378fb63a</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 63}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WATER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Water is a liquid that a beekeeper cannot drink while wearing a veil, adding to the discomfort."&lt;SEP&gt;"Water is a resource that bees collect for drinking and cooling the hive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f2152717d29b2ba8bf6420f9378fb63a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-24ac740bd8207b788e25e1b76a32f657</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 63}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SWARM&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A swarm is a cluster of bees that leaves a colony to find a new home."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f2152717d29b2ba8bf6420f9378fb63a</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 63}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HIVE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"LOCATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A hive is a structure where honey bees live and store honey, symbolized here as 'the hive open and its parts strewn about you'"&lt;SEP&gt;"A hive is the living space of a bee colony, where they live, store food, and raise their young."&lt;SEP&gt;"Hive is a structure where bees live and produce honey, managed by a beekeeper."&lt;SEP&gt;"Hive is a structure where bees live and produce honey, requiring initial setup costs and ongoing maintenance."&lt;SEP&gt;"Hive is the home of the bee colony where bees gather and process nectar."&lt;SEP&gt;"Hive is the living space of the bee colony where all activities take place and where pheromones are exchanged."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-60a04f9021aa4469d11bdecb7939dedb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-495e02b1ab0499af1104889b54b028c2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-24ac740bd8207b788e25e1b76a32f657&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-92d1ecd04d2635b88e1772df1127a05d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e90df7de1c0152a284f55599ac2e855b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f2152717d29b2ba8bf6420f9378fb63a</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 65}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DANGER WARNINGS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Danger warnings are signals bees use to alert others to threats such as predators or environmental hazards."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f2152717d29b2ba8bf6420f9378fb63a</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 63}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SPECIFIC NEEDS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Specific needs within and without the hive refer to the various requirements of the colony, such as food, warmth, and safety."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f2152717d29b2ba8bf6420f9378fb63a</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 63}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ODORS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Odors, or pheromones, are chemical signals that bees use to communicate with each other."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f2152717d29b2ba8bf6420f9378fb63a</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 63}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;INTERPRETATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Interpretation of odors involves bees recognizing and responding to specific pheromone signals."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f2152717d29b2ba8bf6420f9378fb63a</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 63}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;COMMUNICATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Communication among bees includes various methods such as pheromones and dance language."&lt;SEP&gt;"Communication is important for beekeepers to convey information effectively to beginners and other beekeepers."&lt;SEP&gt;"Communication is the act of conveying information or ideas through speech or writing."&lt;SEP&gt;"Communication is the exchange of information between bees, particularly through the waggle dance."&lt;SEP&gt;"Communication is the exchange of information between individuals through speaking, writing, or using some other medium."&lt;SEP&gt;"Communication refers to the exchange of information between the Company and its Subsidiaries and the Unknown Intelligence."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-901cbdf0bd26b111f81dd33ee6c60d30&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-60a04f9021aa4469d11bdecb7939dedb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3702c26fe7454d367a5c70f77e376157&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1a8c54b5dcade8b772c67c1ccfd6db8b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b3c121a5ad657f286818fa5cc9e5c130&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f2152717d29b2ba8bf6420f9378fb63a</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 63}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BEHAVIOR&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Behavior is the way in which someone acts or conducts themselves, especially towards other people."&lt;SEP&gt;"Behavior of individual bees and colonies is influenced by their communication methods and pheromones."&lt;SEP&gt;"Behavior refers to the actions and characteristics of bees, which beekeepers must understand to manage them effectively."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-3702c26fe7454d367a5c70f77e376157&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1a8c54b5dcade8b772c67c1ccfd6db8b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f2152717d29b2ba8bf6420f9378fb63a</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 63}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MOTIVATIONS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Motivations of individual bees and colonies are driven by their communication and the needs of the hive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f2152717d29b2ba8bf6420f9378fb63a</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 63}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ORGANISM&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Organism refers to any living entity that can give off pheromones and respond to them, including bees and other insects."&lt;SEP&gt;"Organism refers to any living thing that can adapt and respond to its environment, particularly in the context of survival mechanisms."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-92d1ecd04d2635b88e1772df1127a05d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-10d5fe05f492cefc74566f590eb23a1a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;QUEEN BEE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Queen Bee is a female bee that gives off an odor in the hive to signal her presence to the colony."&lt;SEP&gt;"Queen Bee is the female reproductive member of the colony, essential for the survival and growth of the hive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-92d1ecd04d2635b88e1772df1127a05d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-699a06af32464879930f06ecbb0af590</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 64}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 130}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BROOD&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Brood refers to the developing offspring of the queen bee, which gives off odors signaling caste and developmental stages."&lt;SEP&gt;"Brood refers to the developing stages of bees within the hive, including eggs, larvae, and pupae."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-92d1ecd04d2635b88e1772df1127a05d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-699a06af32464879930f06ecbb0af590</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 64}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 129}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WORKER BEE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Worker Bee is a female bee that performs various tasks within the colony, including feeding and capping cells based on odors from the brood."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-92d1ecd04d2635b88e1772df1127a05d</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 66}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GUARD BEE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Guard Bee is a type of worker bee responsible for defending the hive entrance and recognizing the correct odor of incoming bees."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-92d1ecd04d2635b88e1772df1127a05d</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 67}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;EMPTY CELL&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Empty Cell is a cell within the hive that has been prepared for an egg by a worker bee, indicated by odors left behind."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-92d1ecd04d2635b88e1772df1127a05d</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 64}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 128}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LOST BEE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Lost Bee is a bee that has become disoriented and uses homing odors to find its way back to the hive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-92d1ecd04d2635b88e1772df1127a05d</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 64}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 131}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CONFUSION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Confusion is a state where bees become disoriented, leading to the release of homing odors to help them find their way back to the hive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-92d1ecd04d2635b88e1772df1127a05d</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 64}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 131}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HOMING ODOR&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Homing Odor is a specific type of odor released by bees to help them navigate back to the hive during periods of confusion."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-92d1ecd04d2635b88e1772df1127a05d</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 64}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 131}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CELL CAPPING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ACTIVITY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Cell Capping is the process performed by worker bees to seal honeycomb cells after the brood has developed into adults."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-92d1ecd04d2635b88e1772df1127a05d</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 66}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FEEDING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ACTIVITY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Feeding is a part of beekeeping management, ensuring bees have adequate nutrition."&lt;SEP&gt;"Feeding is a task performed by worker bees to provide nourishment to the brood and other members of the colony."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-3702c26fe7454d367a5c70f77e376157&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-92d1ecd04d2635b88e1772df1127a05d</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 66}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;QUEEN PRESENCE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Queen Presence is the signal given by the queen bee's pheromones that indicates her presence within the hive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-92d1ecd04d2635b88e1772df1127a05d</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 64}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 130}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BROOD DEVELOPMENT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Brood Development is the process of the brood growing and maturing within the hive, signaled by specific odors emitted by the brood."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-92d1ecd04d2635b88e1772df1127a05d</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 64}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 129}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;INTRUDER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Intruder is a term used to describe any bee or other organism that is not part of the colony and whose presence is detected by guard bees through odors."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-92d1ecd04d2635b88e1772df1127a05d</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 67}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HIVE ENTRANCE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"LOCATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Hive Entrance is the opening of the hive where guard bees monitor and control access to the colony."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-92d1ecd04d2635b88e1772df1127a05d</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 67}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GUARDS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Guards are responsible for repelling intruders based on the odor or lack thereof from a strange bee or other intruder."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-bc1b2a20a73f4da2e13173e3b3d64797</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;COMPANY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Company is a business entity involved in a legal agreement, subject to Bankruptcy Court approvals."&lt;SEP&gt;"Company is a business entity that has filed for bankruptcy and is involved in agreements with supporting lenders and affiliates."&lt;SEP&gt;"Company is a business entity that is part of the agreement and is concerned with material liabilities and ERISA compliance."&lt;SEP&gt;"Company is one of the parties involved in the agreement and is mentioned in the context of mutual termination."&lt;SEP&gt;"Company refers to a business entity that engages in various financial transactions and operations, including tax-related activities."&lt;SEP&gt;"Company refers to the entity entering into an agreement, responsible for cooperating with Supporting Lenders and taking necessary actions to consummate the Transactions."&lt;SEP&gt;"Company refers to the entity making representations and warranties in the agreement, including specific and general representations and warranties."&lt;SEP&gt;"Company refers to the entity that is subject to certain covenants and agreements, and must deliver certificates to supporting lenders."&lt;SEP&gt;"Company refers to the entity that is subject to certain covenants and agreements, and must deliver certificates to supporting lenders.")&lt;SEP&gt;"Company refers to the main entity and its subsidiaries involved in various financial and operational activities, including tax-related actions."&lt;SEP&gt;"Company refers to the main entity involved in the transactions, providing access and information to supporting lenders and their representatives."&lt;SEP&gt;"Company refers to the main entity mentioned in the text, which has certain obligations and liabilities related to retirement and welfare plans."&lt;SEP&gt;"Company refers to the main entity that sponsors plans and reserves the right to amend, terminate, or modify Debtor Plans."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Company is the primary entity responsible for contributions or other amounts payable with respect to the Debtor Plan."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0e8ce67d2107bdd08b0bb31d5ed05831&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9761cab8f6b28df6081e9fb1a2da2a8f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-901cbdf0bd26b111f81dd33ee6c60d30&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-043bdd01778d3f59af7fb1427df2e10b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-60a04f9021aa4469d11bdecb7939dedb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3702c26fe7454d367a5c70f77e376157&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d43b1a9be015da589b0b6eda739a9740&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-495e02b1ab0499af1104889b54b028c2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-54a36509f708a00c7f0056959eeeac48&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1a8c54b5dcade8b772c67c1ccfd6db8b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-58ed7bc84d141ce850aa3bc185a549a1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4c1071a343df40d56b733dc82d134dca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-798070fb4714049d83dcfa2fc51844a1</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 1}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 30}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 109}, {"level": 3, "cluster": 142}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SCOUT BEE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Scout Bee is a type of bee that discovers new sources of nectar and signals the hive about the new source's location and value."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-60a04f9021aa4469d11bdecb7939dedb</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 10}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 69}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BEE COLONY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Bee Colony is a group of bees that work together to gather nectar from various sources, with some bees acting as scouts."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-60a04f9021aa4469d11bdecb7939dedb</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 10}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 68}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NECTAR SOURCE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"LOCATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Nectar Source is a specific area where bees collect nectar, which can be a flower or another plant."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-60a04f9021aa4469d11bdecb7939dedb</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 10}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 68}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TAX REFUND&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Tax Refund is a financial benefit provided by the government to taxpayers, which can be a significant economic value for the company."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-60a04f9021aa4469d11bdecb7939dedb</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 10}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 68}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SUBSIDIARY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Subsidiary is a subsidiary company of the main Company, which can also engage in various financial and operational activities."&lt;SEP&gt;"Subsidiary is a subsidiary of the Company that also has the right to amend, terminate, or modify Debtor Plans."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-495e02b1ab0499af1104889b54b028c2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-60a04f9021aa4469d11bdecb7939dedb</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 1}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 30}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 109}, {"level": 3, "cluster": 143}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ACCOUNTING PERIOD&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Accounting Period is a specific time frame used for preparing financial statements and tax returns."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-60a04f9021aa4469d11bdecb7939dedb</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 1}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 30}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 109}, {"level": 3, "cluster": 142}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;AMENDED TAX RETURN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Amended Tax Return is a tax form filed to correct errors or changes in a previous tax return."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-60a04f9021aa4469d11bdecb7939dedb</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 1}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 30}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 109}, {"level": 3, "cluster": 142}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MATERIAL ELECTION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Material Election is a significant decision made by the Company or its Subsidiaries regarding taxes."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-60a04f9021aa4469d11bdecb7939dedb</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 1}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 30}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 109}, {"level": 3, "cluster": 142}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TAX&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Tax is a financial charge imposed by the government on individuals or organizations for various purposes."&lt;SEP&gt;"Tax refers to financial obligations related to the Company and its subsidiaries, including returns, elections, and claims."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-58ed7bc84d141ce850aa3bc185a549a1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-60a04f9021aa4469d11bdecb7939dedb</data>
