<node id="&quot;RESONANCE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Resonance is a phenomenon that affects the production of vowel sounds in the human voice."&lt;SEP&gt;"Resonance refers to the amplification of sound by the natural acoustic properties of the vocal tract, which can vary depending on the shape of the vowels."&lt;SEP&gt;"Resonance refers to the amplification of sound within the vocal tract, affecting the quality and color of the voice."&lt;SEP&gt;"Resonance refers to the amplification of sound within the vocal tract, which can influence the quality and projection of the singing voice."</data>
