</node>
<node id="&quot;VIBRATO&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Vibrato is a technique in singing where the pitch of a note is rapidly and repeatedly varied, creating a wavy effect."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-3701e1e7b87348b03a3427f01667b3d5</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 43}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 122}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HARMONICS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Harmonics refer to the natural overtones produced by a vibrating system, such as a singer's voice, and their intensity can be analyzed using spectrum analyzers."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-3701e1e7b87348b03a3427f01667b3d5</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 43}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 122}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FORMANTS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Formants are acoustic properties that contribute to the quality of speech and singing, unrelated to bee behavior."&lt;SEP&gt;"Formants are specific frequencies in the human voice that contribute to its timbre and help in creating distinct sounds and vowels."&lt;SEP&gt;"Formants are the resonant frequencies of the vocal tract that give a vowel its characteristic quality and can be analyzed using spectrum analyzers."&lt;SEP&gt;"Formants are the resonant frequencies of the vocal tract that give different vowels their characteristic sounds."&lt;SEP&gt;"Formants are vocal resonances that affect the quality of sound produced by the vocal tract."&lt;SEP&gt;"Formants refer to the resonant frequencies of the vocal tract that create vowel sounds."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-36d0dcb2c223d1d1ceee0146324df75b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3701e1e7b87348b03a3427f01667b3d5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9236dc00dbccfcc24cbcf791124687a5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9df53a9e4f0e74a05d58e93589ff4804&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e8e95cffe887226367f1fc5b800af6dc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-925befdcde977c2787b77c4826eba91f</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 43}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 120}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NASAL TONE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A nasal tone in singing refers to a sound that is produced with a greater emphasis on the nasal passages, which can be analyzed using spectrum analyzers."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-3701e1e7b87348b03a3427f01667b3d5</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 43}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 120}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;INTONATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Intonation refers to the accuracy of a singer's pitch, and there are software tools available to help improve it."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-3701e1e7b87348b03a3427f01667b3d5</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 43}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 121}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MUSICIANSHIP SKILLS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Musicianship skills include a range of abilities such as reading music, understanding harmony, and developing a sense of rhythm, which can be enhanced with the help of technology."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-3701e1e7b87348b03a3427f01667b3d5</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 43}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 121}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LIPS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ANATOMY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Lips are a part of the body used for speaking and singing, contributing to the articulatory life of a singer."&lt;SEP&gt;"Lips are soft tissues that help in producing certain sounds and articulations."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-3701e1e7b87348b03a3427f01667b3d5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9236dc00dbccfcc24cbcf791124687a5</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 19}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 89}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TONGUE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ANATOMY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The tongue is a muscular organ in the mouth that is essential for speech, swallowing, and tasting, and is connected to the hyoid bone."&lt;SEP&gt;"Tongue is a muscular organ that helps in producing vowel sounds and articulating words."&lt;SEP&gt;"Tongue is a part of the body used for speaking and singing, contributing to the articulatory life of a singer."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-3701e1e7b87348b03a3427f01667b3d5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-774ba8ad52bdff605cf6f70d4eef41f6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9236dc00dbccfcc24cbcf791124687a5</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 19}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 89}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DYNAMIC LEVELS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Dynamic Levels refer to the range of volume in singing, from very soft to very loud, which is part of the articulatory life of a singer."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-3701e1e7b87348b03a3427f01667b3d5</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 19}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 88}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SHORT NOTES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Short Notes are brief musical phrases or sounds, which are part of the articulatory life of a singer."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-3701e1e7b87348b03a3427f01667b3d5</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 19}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 88}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LONG NOTES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Long Notes are sustained musical phrases or sounds, which are part of the articulatory life of a singer."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-3701e1e7b87348b03a3427f01667b3d5</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 19}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 88}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ACCENTS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Accents are stress or emphasis on certain syllables or words, which are part of the articulatory life of a singer."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-3701e1e7b87348b03a3427f01667b3d5</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 19}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 88}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CRESCENDOS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Crescendos are gradual increases in volume or intensity, which are part of the articulatory life of a singer."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-3701e1e7b87348b03a3427f01667b3d5</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 19}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 88}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DIMINUENDOS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Diminuendos are gradual decreases in volume or intensity, which are part of the articulatory life of a singer."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-3701e1e7b87348b03a3427f01667b3d5</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 19}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 88}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;UNION STATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Union Station is a metaphorical term used to describe the anatomical structure where various parts of the body, including the tongue, larynx, throat, jaw, and palate, are interconnected."&lt;SEP&gt;"Union Station refers to the complex interconnection of anatomical parts such as the tongue, larynx, throat, jaw, and palate, which are all involved in speech production."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-774ba8ad52bdff605cf6f70d4eef41f6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9236dc00dbccfcc24cbcf791124687a5</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PIANISSIMOS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Pianissimos refers to a very soft dynamic level in music."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9236dc00dbccfcc24cbcf791124687a5</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 19}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 89}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FORTES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Fortes refers to a loud dynamic level in music."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9236dc00dbccfcc24cbcf791124687a5</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 19}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 89}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;POWER SUPPLY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Power supply refers to the force used by singers to produce different musical articulations."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9236dc00dbccfcc24cbcf791124687a5</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 19}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 89}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;VOCAL TRACT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The vocal tract is the pathway through which sound travels from the vocal folds to the mouth, where formants are produced to create speech and singing."&lt;SEP&gt;"Vocal tract refers to the pathway through which sound is produced and modified in the human body."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9236dc00dbccfcc24cbcf791124687a5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-925befdcde977c2787b77c4826eba91f</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 19}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 89}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;JAW&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGAN"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Jaw is a skeletal structure that supports the tongue and helps in shaping the vocal tract."&lt;SEP&gt;"The jaw is a critical structure for opening and closing the mouth, and is connected to the hyoid bone."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-774ba8ad52bdff605cf6f70d4eef41f6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9236dc00dbccfcc24cbcf791124687a5</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 19}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 89}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PALATE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGAN"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Palate is the roof of the mouth that helps in shaping the vocal tract and producing certain sounds."&lt;SEP&gt;"The palate is the roof of the mouth, playing a vital role in speech and swallowing, and is interconnected with the hyoid bone."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-774ba8ad52bdff605cf6f70d4eef41f6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9236dc00dbccfcc24cbcf791124687a5</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 19}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 89}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TUESDAY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Tuesday is a day of the week and is mentioned as an example of a word with multiple vowel sounds."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9236dc00dbccfcc24cbcf791124687a5</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HYOID BONE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The hyoid bone is a small, U-shaped bone located in the neck, suspended below the jaw, and serves as a critical suspension point for the larynx and the root of the tongue."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-774ba8ad52bdff605cf6f70d4eef41f6</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PATELLAE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Patellae, also known as kneecaps, are two small sesamoid bones located in the knee joint, which do not connect to other bones via a joint."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-774ba8ad52bdff605cf6f70d4eef41f6</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NATURE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Nature refers to the natural world and its processes, which conspire against us to make it difficult to achieve independence in the articulatory structures required for good singing."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-774ba8ad52bdff605cf6f70d4eef41f6</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;INDEPENDENCE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Independence refers to the ability to act or exist independently, which is challenging due to the interconnections in the articulatory structures."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-774ba8ad52bdff605cf6f70d4eef41f6</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;EXECUTIVE EMPLOYMENT OR SEVERANCE PLAN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
