<node id="&quot;SIX-YEAR PERIOD&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Six-Year Period refers to the time frame of six years prior to the date of the Agreement during which the Company and its Subsidiaries have not maintained, established, sponsored, participated in, contributed to, or been obligated to contribute to any multiemployer plans."&lt;SEP&gt;"Six-Year Period refers to the time frame within which certain actions must not have occurred to avoid penalties."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d43b1a9be015da589b0b6eda739a9740&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-901cbdf0bd26b111f81dd33ee6c60d30</data>
