  <data key="d2">chunk-901cbdf0bd26b111f81dd33ee6c60d30</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CODE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The Code refers to the Internal Revenue Code, which includes provisions such as Section 412 that pertain to multiemployer plans, which the Company and its Subsidiaries have never maintained, established, sponsored, participated in, contributed to, or been obligated to contribute to."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-901cbdf0bd26b111f81dd33ee6c60d30</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MODIFICATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Modification refers to the act of changing a plan, which the Company or its Subsidiary reserves the right to do at any time for any Debtor Plan that provides retiree or post-employment benefits."</data>
