  <data key="d1">"A Sting is an incident where a bee injects venom into the skin of a beekeeper, causing pain and sometimes allergic reactions."&lt;SEP&gt;"A sting is a defensive behavior of honey bees, causing irritation to the beekeeper, mentioned as 'stings are usually but a minor irritation'"&lt;SEP&gt;"Sting is a defensive behavior used by bees to protect their colony, home, and stored honey."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-925befdcde977c2787b77c4826eba91f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e90df7de1c0152a284f55599ac2e855b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-24ac740bd8207b788e25e1b76a32f657</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 65}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PANTS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Pants are part of a beekeeper's attire that can be penetrated by bees, leading to the sensation of a bee crawling inside."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-24ac740bd8207b788e25e1b76a32f657</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LEG&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"BODY_PART"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Leg is a body part that can be affected by a bee crawling inside, causing discomfort and concern."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-24ac740bd8207b788e25e1b76a32f657</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;KNEE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"BODY_PART"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Knee is a specific body part that can be affected by a bee crawling inside, causing significant discomfort."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-24ac740bd8207b788e25e1b76a32f657</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CLOTHING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Clothing is part of a beekeeper's attire that can pinch a bee, causing it to sting."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-24ac740bd8207b788e25e1b76a32f657</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HAND&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"BODY_PART"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Hand is a body part that can be used to slap a bee to kill it, but it can also be stung if the bee is inside the hand."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-24ac740bd8207b788e25e1b76a32f657</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NOSE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"BODY_PART"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Nose is a body part that can be restricted by a veil, making it difficult to breathe or blow."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-24ac740bd8207b788e25e1b76a32f657</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;POLLINATOR&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ROLE"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Pollinator is a role played by bees in the ecosystem, contributing to plant reproduction and biodiversity."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-24ac740bd8207b788e25e1b76a32f657</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;OPEN HIVE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"STATE"</data>
  <data key="d1">"An Open Hive is a state where the hive is not closed, allowing beekeepers to access and work within it."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-24ac740bd8207b788e25e1b76a32f657</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CLOSED HIVE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"STATE"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A Closed Hive is a state where the hive is sealed, protecting the bees and preventing unauthorized access."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-24ac740bd8207b788e25e1b76a32f657</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NEGATIVE EXPERIENCES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Negative experiences refer to challenging moments in beekeeping that are soon forgotten, such as the discomfort of being in the beeyard."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e90df7de1c0152a284f55599ac2e855b</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 65}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;POSITIVE EXPERIENCES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Positive experiences include the enjoyment and enthusiasm of beekeepers, as well as the calmness and serenity of the beeyard on a pleasant summer day."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e90df7de1c0152a284f55599ac2e855b</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 65}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CALMNESS AND SERENITY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Calmness and serenity describe the peaceful atmosphere in a beeyard on a pleasant summer day, which beekeepers enjoy."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e90df7de1c0152a284f55599ac2e855b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PLAY TIME&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ACTIVITY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Play time refers to the leisurely activities of bees, which beekeepers observe and appreciate."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e90df7de1c0152a284f55599ac2e855b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GATHERING OF BEEKEEPERS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A gathering of beekeepers is a social event where they share their enthusiasm and discuss their experiences."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e90df7de1c0152a284f55599ac2e855b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DOWN SIDE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The down side includes the challenges and negative experiences in beekeeping, such as stings and discomfort."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e90df7de1c0152a284f55599ac2e855b</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 65}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PREDATORS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Predators refer to animals that pose a threat to bee colonies, leading to the need for defensive behaviors like stinging."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-925befdcde977c2787b77c4826eba91f</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WINTER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Winter is a season during which bees must survive using stored resources, emphasizing the importance of their defensive behaviors."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-925befdcde977c2787b77c4826eba91f</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;VOWELS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Vowels are sounds produced by the combination of formants F1 and F2, which are essential for creating the basic units of speech."&lt;SEP&gt;"Vowels are the sounds produced by the mouth without obstruction, and they are crucial for vocal production and communication."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e8e95cffe887226367f1fc5b800af6dc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-925befdcde977c2787b77c4826eba91f</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 44}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TIMBRE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Timbre is the unique quality of a sound, contributed to by higher formants and other factors, which gives voices their individual characteristics."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-925befdcde977c2787b77c4826eba91f</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;RAW, BUZZING SOUND&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The raw, buzzing sound produced by the vocal folds before it is modified by the vocal tract."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-925befdcde977c2787b77c4826eba91f</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;F1&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"F1 is the first formant in a phonetic sequence, used to create vowels and contribute to the overall timbre of a voice."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9df53a9e4f0e74a05d58e93589ff4804</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 43}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 120}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;F2&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"F2 is the second formant in a phonetic sequence, used to create vowels and contribute to the overall timbre of a voice."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9df53a9e4f0e74a05d58e93589ff4804</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 43}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 120}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SINGER'S FORMANT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Singer's formant is a cluster of formants three through five, used in opera singing to create a ringing sound and enable the voice to be heard without amplification."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9df53a9e4f0e74a05d58e93589ff4804</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 43}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 120}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;OPERA&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Opera is a form of musical theater where singers perform a dramatic work combining text (libretto) and musical score, often involving complex vocal techniques such as the use of formants."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9df53a9e4f0e74a05d58e93589ff4804</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 43}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 120}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;B-FLAT3&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"B-flat3 is a musical note in the bass range, used as a starting point for an ascending scale in the given context."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9df53a9e4f0e74a05d58e93589ff4804</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 44}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;D-NATURAL&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"D-natural is a musical note in the middle range, used in the given context to demonstrate the effect of formants on voice production."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9df53a9e4f0e74a05d58e93589ff4804</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 44}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;E-FLAT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"E-flat is a musical note in the middle range, used in the given context to demonstrate the effect of formants on voice production."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9df53a9e4f0e74a05d58e93589ff4804</data>
