</node>
<node id="&quot;VOWEL /EE/">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Vowel /ee/ is a specific sound produced in the mouth, influenced by formants and contributing to the overall quality of the voice."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9df53a9e4f0e74a05d58e93589ff4804</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 46}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;VOWEL /OO/">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Vowel /oo/ is another specific sound produced in the mouth, influenced by formants and contributing to the overall quality of the voice."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9df53a9e4f0e74a05d58e93589ff4804</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 43}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 120}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;RUSTLING LEAF&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Rustling leaf is an analogy for the wind, indicating that formants are similarly invisible yet observable through their effects."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9df53a9e4f0e74a05d58e93589ff4804</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BREEZE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Breeze is another analogy for the wind, further emphasizing the concept."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9df53a9e4f0e74a05d58e93589ff4804</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SOUND&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Sound is changed through the action of formants, making them directly responsible for altering the sound."&lt;SEP&gt;"Sound refers to the quality and characteristics of vocal production, which can be influenced by various factors such as formants and vowels."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9df53a9e4f0e74a05d58e93589ff4804&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e8e95cffe887226367f1fc5b800af6dc</data>
