  <data key="d1">"Sustaining the vowel /ee/ allows for the demonstration of formant effects."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9df53a9e4f0e74a05d58e93589ff4804</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 46}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CHANGE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ACTION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Change in sound is due to the alignment of the scale tone and formants."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9df53a9e4f0e74a05d58e93589ff4804</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 43}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 120}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;AMPLIFICATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EFFECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Amplification occurs when the scale tone and formant are on the same pitch."&lt;SEP&gt;"Amplification refers to the increase in the volume or intensity of sound, which can be achieved through various means including formants."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9df53a9e4f0e74a05d58e93589ff4804&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e8e95cffe887226367f1fc5b800af6dc</data>
