  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"ee is a vowel that corresponds to the pitch E4 in a C-Major triad in first inversion, open position, according to the mnemonic 'every child gets candy eagerly'."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e8e95cffe887226367f1fc5b800af6dc</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;EH&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"eh is a vowel that corresponds to the pitch C5 in a C-Major triad in first inversion, open position, according to the mnemonic 'every child gets candy eagerly'."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e8e95cffe887226367f1fc5b800af6dc</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;AH&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"ah is a vowel that corresponds to the pitch G5 in a C-Major triad in first inversion, open position, according to the mnemonic 'every child gets candy eagerly'."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e8e95cffe887226367f1fc5b800af6dc</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;OH&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"oh is a vowel that corresponds to the pitch C5 in a C-Major triad in first inversion, open position, according to the mnemonic 'every child gets candy eagerly'."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e8e95cffe887226367f1fc5b800af6dc</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;OO&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"oo is a vowel that corresponds to the pitch E4 in a C-Major triad in first inversion, open position, according to the mnemonic 'every child gets candy eagerly'."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e8e95cffe887226367f1fc5b800af6dc</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;C-MAJOR TRIAD IN FIRST INVERSION, OPEN POSITION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"C-Major triad in first inversion, open position is a musical structure used as a reference for the approximate pitches of the first formants for the main vowels."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e8e95cffe887226367f1fc5b800af6dc</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;E4&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"E4 is the pitch corresponding to the ee and oo vowels in a C-Major triad in first inversion, open position, according to the mnemonic 'every child gets candy eagerly'."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e8e95cffe887226367f1fc5b800af6dc</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;C5&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"C5 is the pitch corresponding to the eh and oh vowels in a C-Major triad in first inversion, open position, according to the mnemonic 'every child gets candy eagerly'."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e8e95cffe887226367f1fc5b800af6dc</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;G5&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"G5 is the pitch corresponding to the ah vowel in a C-Major triad in first inversion, open position, according to the mnemonic 'every child gets candy eagerly'."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e8e95cffe887226367f1fc5b800af6dc</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MINOR THIRD&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A minor third is the interval within which formants typically vary, no farther than that, before the vowel must change."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e8e95cffe887226367f1fc5b800af6dc</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MIDDLE-C&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Middle-C is a specific pitch in music, often used as a reference point for tuning instruments."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e8e95cffe887226367f1fc5b800af6dc</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 44}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PITCH&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Pitch is the perceived frequency of a sound, which affects the clarity of vowel sounds produced by singers."&lt;SEP&gt;"Pitch refers to the perceived frequency of a sound, which can affect the quality and clarity of vocal production."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-b3c121a5ad657f286818fa5cc9e5c130&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e8e95cffe887226367f1fc5b800af6dc</data>
