</node>
<node id="&quot;MUSIC THEORY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Music theory is the study of how music works, including the structure, composition, and analysis of music."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e8e95cffe887226367f1fc5b800af6dc</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;INTERVAL&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Interval refers to the difference in pitch between two notes, measured in semitones or other units."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e8e95cffe887226367f1fc5b800af6dc</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FORMANT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Formant is a specific frequency component of a sound, particularly important in vowel production and amplification of harmonics."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-b3c121a5ad657f286818fa5cc9e5c130</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 6}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 52}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;VOWEL&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Vowel is a type of sound produced by humans using the vocal tract, characterized by the absence of complete closure of the vocal tract at any point during its production."&lt;SEP&gt;"Vowel refers to a sound produced by humans in which the vocal tract is obstructed in such a way that there is a relatively continuous flow of airstream through a narrow channel."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-b3c121a5ad657f286818fa5cc9e5c130&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-99acddd9749381623926152b0e762491</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 6}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 54}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HARMONIC&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Harmonic is a component of a complex sound wave that is an integer multiple of the fundamental frequency."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-b3c121a5ad657f286818fa5cc9e5c130</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 6}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 53}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MEN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Men refer to adult males, who can produce clear vowel sounds when singing low pitches due to the presence of a harmonic close to a formant."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-b3c121a5ad657f286818fa5cc9e5c130</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 6}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 53}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WOMEN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Women are a group of performers in music theater, whose vocal ranges have also blurred over time."&lt;SEP&gt;"Women refer to adult females, who may struggle to produce clear vowel sounds when singing high pitches, especially sopranos."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-b3c121a5ad657f286818fa5cc9e5c130&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4c547b7067138396efde8a5c09f25f67</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 6}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 53}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SOPRANO&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ROLE"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Soprano is a high female singing voice, often used in opera and classical music."&lt;SEP&gt;"Soprano is a vocal classification for female singers, typically with a high vocal range, used in classical singing and sometimes in music theater."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-b3c121a5ad657f286818fa5cc9e5c130&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-473d49a0693de7af12ba5761335f08ae</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 6}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 53}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;OPERA SINGER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
