</node>
<node id="&quot;AUDIENCE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Audience is the group of people who listen to the performance, who may not be able to distinguish between certain vowels if formants and pitches do not match."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-b3c121a5ad657f286818fa5cc9e5c130</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 6}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 52}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FUNDAMENTAL FREQUENCY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Fundamental Frequency is the lowest frequency of a complex sound, which is an integer multiple of the formants."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-b3c121a5ad657f286818fa5cc9e5c130</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FIRST FORMANT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"First Formant is the lowest formant of a vowel, which is crucial for identifying certain vowels like /ee/ when the pitch is high."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-b3c121a5ad657f286818fa5cc9e5c130</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 6}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 54}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PHRASE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Phrase is a group of words forming a unit of speech, often used in singing to convey a specific meaning."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-b3c121a5ad657f286818fa5cc9e5c130</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 6}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 54}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LEAVE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Leave is a word in English, represented phonetically as /liːv/, which requires a specific formant to be clearly heard."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-b3c121a5ad657f286818fa5cc9e5c130</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LOVE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Love is a word in English, represented phonetically as /lʌv/, which can be confused with 'leave' when formants and pitches do not match."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-b3c121a5ad657f286818fa5cc9e5c130</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FOREVER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Forever is a word in English, represented phonetically as /fərˈevər/, which can be part of the phrase 'leave forever' but may sound different based on formant and pitch."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-b3c121a5ad657f286818fa5cc9e5c130</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LOW PITCHES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Low Pitches refers to the range of frequencies that men can produce clear vowel sounds."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-b3c121a5ad657f286818fa5cc9e5c130</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HIGH PITCHES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"High Pitches refers to the range of frequencies that women, especially sopranos, may struggle to produce clear vowel sounds."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-b3c121a5ad657f286818fa5cc9e5c130</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CLEAR VOWEL SOUNDS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Clear Vowel Sounds is the result of formants and harmonics aligning correctly."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-b3c121a5ad657f286818fa5cc9e5c130</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;INGÉNUE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Ingénue is a young, innocent female character often found in classic music theater shows."</data>
