  <data key="d2">chunk-36d0dcb2c223d1d1ceee0146324df75b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SECOND FORMANTS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Second Formants are important for opera singers but less so for others, tracking specific vowel sounds at high pitches."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-36d0dcb2c223d1d1ceee0146324df75b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CANNON&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Cannon is a researcher who conducted studies on the effects of emotional stress on the digestive system."&lt;SEP&gt;"Cannon is a researcher who noticed the inhibition of gastric activity and hypothesized about the involvement of the adrenal glands in the body's response to fear and anger."&lt;SEP&gt;"Cannon is a scientist who made significant contributions to understanding the hypothalamus and its role in the fight-or-flight response."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a1d8d02f1a378aeda801147f5f55de20&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-36d0dcb2c223d1d1ceee0146324df75b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-10d5fe05f492cefc74566f590eb23a1a</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 45}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;VAGUS NERVE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Vagus Nerve is a cranial nerve that Cannon studied for its role in the inhibition of peristalsis."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-36d0dcb2c223d1d1ceee0146324df75b</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 45}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SPLANCHNIC NERVE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Splanchnic Nerve is part of the sympathetic nervous system that Cannon studied for its role in the inhibition of peristalsis."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-36d0dcb2c223d1d1ceee0146324df75b</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 45}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DIGESTIVE ORGANS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Digestive Organs are the focus of Cannon's studies on how emotional stress affects their function."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-36d0dcb2c223d1d1ceee0146324df75b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PERISTALSIS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Peristalsis is the muscular contraction of the digestive tract that Cannon studied in relation to emotional stress."&lt;SEP&gt;"Peristalsis is the muscular contraction of the digestive tract that moves food along, which Cannon initially studied in relation to emotional responses."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a1d8d02f1a378aeda801147f5f55de20&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-36d0dcb2c223d1d1ceee0146324df75b</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 45}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FEAR&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Fear is an emotional response that Cannon and de la Paz studied in relation to the body's physiological reactions."&lt;SEP&gt;"Fear is an emotional response to perceived threats, which can trigger the release of epinephrine and the stress response."&lt;SEP&gt;"Fear is an emotional stimulus that Cannon used to induce inhibition of peristalsis in his studies."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6a2f473ed4702ee40d264f9c881963ad&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a1d8d02f1a378aeda801147f5f55de20&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-36d0dcb2c223d1d1ceee0146324df75b</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 45}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GASTRIC ACTIVITY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Gastric Activity is the function of the stomach that Cannon noticed often continues after the provoking factor is gone."&lt;SEP&gt;"Gastric activity refers to the movement and secretion processes in the stomach, which Cannon observed to be inhibited by emotional responses."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a1d8d02f1a378aeda801147f5f55de20&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-36d0dcb2c223d1d1ceee0146324df75b</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 45}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MUSICAL PITCHES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Musical Pitches are the tones produced by musical instruments or voices."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-36d0dcb2c223d1d1ceee0146324df75b</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 45}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;EMOTIONAL STRESS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Emotional Stress is a psychological state that can affect various bodily functions, including digestion."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-36d0dcb2c223d1d1ceee0146324df75b</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 45}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;STOMACH&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Stomach is part of the digestive system that Cannon studied for its response to emotional stress."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-36d0dcb2c223d1d1ceee0146324df75b</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 45}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;INTESTINES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Intestines are part of the digestive system that Cannon studied for its response to emotional stress."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-36d0dcb2c223d1d1ceee0146324df75b</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 45}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CRUDE STUDIES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Crude Studies are the initial, basic experiments conducted by Cannon to understand the effects of emotional stress on the digestive system."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-36d0dcb2c223d1d1ceee0146324df75b</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 45}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;INHIBITION OF PERISTALSIS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Inhibition of Peristalsis is the reduction in the muscular contractions of the digestive tract that Cannon studied."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-36d0dcb2c223d1d1ceee0146324df75b</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 45}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SYMPATHETIC SYSTEM&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Sympathetic System is part of the autonomic nervous system that Cannon studied for its role in the inhibition of peristalsis."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-36d0dcb2c223d1d1ceee0146324df75b</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 45}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CRANIAL SYSTEM&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Cranial System is part of the nervous system that includes the Vagus Nerve, which Cannon studied."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-36d0dcb2c223d1d1ceee0146324df75b</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 45}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DIGESTIVE SYSTEM&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Digestive System is the entire system that Cannon studied for its response to emotional stress."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-36d0dcb2c223d1d1ceee0146324df75b</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 45}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DANIEL DE LA PAZ&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Daniel de la Paz is a young physician who assisted Cannon in conducting experiments involving the effects of fear and anger on cats."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a1d8d02f1a378aeda801147f5f55de20</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ADRENAL GLANDS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGAN"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Adrenal Glands are endocrine glands located on top of the kidneys that produce hormones such as epinephrine and cortisol, playing a crucial role in the body's stress response."&lt;SEP&gt;"Adrenal glands are endocrine glands that produce adrenalin, a substance that Cannon believed might be involved in the body's response to fear and anger."&lt;SEP&gt;"Adrenal glands are endocrine glands that produce adrenalin, a substance that can affect the body's response to fear and anger."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6a2f473ed4702ee40d264f9c881963ad&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a1d8d02f1a378aeda801147f5f55de20</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 38}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SYMPATHETIC NERVOUS SYSTEM&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Sympathetic Nervous System is part of the autonomic nervous system that prepares the body for emergency situations, such as fight or flight."&lt;SEP&gt;"The sympathetic nervous system is a branch of the autonomic nervous system that Cannon studied as a key player in the body's response to fear and anger."&lt;SEP&gt;"The sympathetic nervous system is a branch of the autonomic nervous system that connects to various glands and smooth muscles to maintain homeostasis and to mediate the fight-or-flight response."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6a2f473ed4702ee40d264f9c881963ad&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a1d8d02f1a378aeda801147f5f55de20</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 39}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ANGER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Anger is an emotional response to frustration or provocation, which can trigger the release of epinephrine and the stress response."&lt;SEP&gt;"Anger is another emotional response that Cannon and de la Paz investigated in their experiments."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6a2f473ed4702ee40d264f9c881963ad&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a1d8d02f1a378aeda801147f5f55de20</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 37}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ADRENALIN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"SUBSTANCE"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Adrenalin is a substance extracted from the adrenal glands that Cannon hypothesized might be involved in the body's response to fear and anger."&lt;SEP&gt;"Adrenalin is a substance extracted from the adrenal glands that Cannon hypothesized might be responsible for the body's response to fear and anger."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a1d8d02f1a378aeda801147f5f55de20</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HOMEOSTASIS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Homeostasis is the maintenance of a stable internal environment in the body, which is regulated by various physiological processes."&lt;SEP&gt;"Homeostasis is the maintenance of stable internal conditions in the body, which the sympathetic nervous system helps to regulate."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6a2f473ed4702ee40d264f9c881963ad&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a1d8d02f1a378aeda801147f5f55de20</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 38}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CATS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANISM"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Cats are the subjects of Cannon and de la Paz's experiments, used to study the effects of fear and anger on the body."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a1d8d02f1a378aeda801147f5f55de20</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BARKING DOGS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Barking dogs are the source of stress used to provoke fear in the cats during Cannon and de la Paz's experiments."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a1d8d02f1a378aeda801147f5f55de20</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BLOOD SAMPLES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"SAMPLE"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Blood samples were collected from the cats before and after exposure to barking dogs to study the effects of fear on the body."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a1d8d02f1a378aeda801147f5f55de20</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ISOLATED INTESTINAL MUSCLE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANISM"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Isolated intestinal muscle was used to test the effects of adrenalin and the substance found in frightened cat blood."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a1d8d02f1a378aeda801147f5f55de20</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;STRESS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Stress is the condition experienced by the cats when exposed to barking dogs, which Cannon and de la Paz used to study the body's response."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a1d8d02f1a378aeda801147f5f55de20</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MUSCLE CONTRACTION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PROCESS"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Muscle contraction is the process observed in the isolated intestinal muscle to test the effects of adrenalin and the substance found in frightened cat blood."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a1d8d02f1a378aeda801147f5f55de20</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SMALL STRIP&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TOOL"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A small strip was used to isolate the intestinal muscle for testing purposes."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a1d8d02f1a378aeda801147f5f55de20</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;INJECTION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PROCEDURE"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Injection is the method used to introduce adrenalin into the bloodstream of the cats and the isolated intestinal muscle."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a1d8d02f1a378aeda801147f5f55de20</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CENTRAL PORTION OF THE ADRENAL GLANDS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ANATOMY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The central portion of the adrenal glands is the source of adrenalin, which Cannon hypothesized might be involved in the body's response to fear and anger."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a1d8d02f1a378aeda801147f5f55de20</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BLOODSTREAM&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ANATOMY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The bloodstream is the pathway through which adrenalin is introduced and travels to affect the body's response."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a1d8d02f1a378aeda801147f5f55de20</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NERVES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Nerves are part of the nervous system that transmit signals throughout the body, particularly in response to stress and pain."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6a2f473ed4702ee40d264f9c881963ad</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CRANIAL REGION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Cranial Region refers to the area around the brain, which contains nerves that generally act in opposition to those from the thoraco-lumbar region."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6a2f473ed4702ee40d264f9c881963ad</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SACRAL REGION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Sacral Region is part of the spinal cord located at the base of the spine, containing nerves that generally act in opposition to those from the thoraco-lumbar region."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6a2f473ed4702ee40d264f9c881963ad</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;THORACO-LUMBAR REGION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Thoraco-Lumbar Region is part of the spinal cord extending from the chest to the lower back, containing nerves that generally act in opposition to those from the cranial and sacral regions."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6a2f473ed4702ee40d264f9c881963ad</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;EPINEPHRINE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Epinephrine is a hormone produced by the adrenal glands that speeds up heart rate, releases sugar from the liver, and promotes blood clotting, among other effects."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6a2f473ed4702ee40d264f9c881963ad</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 37}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HEART RATE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Heart Rate refers to the number of times the heart beats per minute, which is increased by epinephrine during stress."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6a2f473ed4702ee40d264f9c881963ad</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 37}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SUGAR RELEASE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Sugar Release is the process of releasing glucose from the liver into the bloodstream, stimulated by epinephrine during stress."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6a2f473ed4702ee40d264f9c881963ad</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 37}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BLOOD CLOTTING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Blood Clotting is the process of forming clots to stop bleeding, which is promoted by epinephrine during stress."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6a2f473ed4702ee40d264f9c881963ad</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 37}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PAIN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Pain is a sensation caused by injury or illness, which can trigger the release of epinephrine and the stress response."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6a2f473ed4702ee40d264f9c881963ad</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 37}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ADRENAL SYSTEM&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Adrenal System includes the adrenal glands and the sympathetic nervous system, working together to modulate body organs in stressful conditions."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6a2f473ed4702ee40d264f9c881963ad</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 39}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DARWIN'S PRINCIPLE OF NATURAL SELECTION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Darwin's Principle of Natural Selection is the theory that organisms better adapted to their environment are more likely to survive and reproduce."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6a2f473ed4702ee40d264f9c881963ad</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ADRENAL RESPONSES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Adrenal Responses include the release of hormones like epinephrine in response to stressors such as pain, fear, or anger, preparing the body for fight or flight."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6a2f473ed4702ee40d264f9c881963ad</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WALTER B. CANNON&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Walter B. Cannon is the author of 'The Wisdom of the Body', known for his work on the body's stress response and the role of the adrenal glands."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6a2f473ed4702ee40d264f9c881963ad</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 37}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FLIGHT-OR-FIGHT RESPONSE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Flight-or-Fight Response is the body's reaction to perceived threats, involving the activation of the sympathetic nervous system and the release of hormones like epinephrine."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6a2f473ed4702ee40d264f9c881963ad</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 38}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ADRENAL MEDULLA&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Adrenal Medulla is the inner part of the adrenal gland that produces catecholamines, including epinephrine."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6a2f473ed4702ee40d264f9c881963ad</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 38}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ADRENAL CORTEX&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Adrenal Cortex is the outer part of the adrenal gland that produces corticosteroids, which are important for metabolism and stress response."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6a2f473ed4702ee40d264f9c881963ad</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 38}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LIVER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Liver is an organ that stores and releases glucose, and is involved in the production of glucose during stress through the process of glycogenolysis."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6a2f473ed4702ee40d264f9c881963ad</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 37}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MUSCLES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Muscles are tissues that contract to produce movement, and are supplied with blood during the fight or flight response to meet increased energy demands."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6a2f473ed4702ee40d264f9c881963ad</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 37}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FATIGUE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Fatigue is a state of physical or mental exhaustion, which can be reduced by the release of epinephrine and other hormones."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6a2f473ed4702ee40d264f9c881963ad</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 37}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BLOOD&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Blood is the fluid tissue that circulates throughout the body, carrying oxygen, nutrients, and hormones to cells and removing waste products."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6a2f473ed4702ee40d264f9c881963ad</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 37}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;RUN OR FIGHT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Run or Fight is the body's immediate response to a perceived threat, involving the mobilization of energy and resources to either flee or confront the threat."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6a2f473ed4702ee40d264f9c881963ad</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 37}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NATURAL SELECTION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Natural Selection is the process by which certain traits become more or less common in a population over time due to their effect on survival and reproduction."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6a2f473ed4702ee40d264f9c881963ad</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SURVIVAL&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Survival is the ability to live and remain healthy, which is enhanced by the body's stress response and the mobilization of resources."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6a2f473ed4702ee40d264f9c881963ad</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;REPRODUCTION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Reproduction is the process by which organisms create offspring, which is facilitated by the body's stress response in terms of energy allocation and hormonal balance."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6a2f473ed4702ee40d264f9c881963ad</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PHILIP BARD&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Philip Bard is Cannon's student who demonstrated the critical role of the hypothalamus in controlling involuntary functions such as digestion, heart rate, respiration, and the fight-or-flight response."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-10d5fe05f492cefc74566f590eb23a1a</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 45}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HYPOTHALAMUS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The hypothalamus is a part of the brain that controls involuntary functions such as digestion, heart rate, respiration, and the fight-or-flight response."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-10d5fe05f492cefc74566f590eb23a1a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FIGHT-OR-FLIGHT RESPONSE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The fight-or-flight response is an emergency response mechanism that helps organisms avoid danger and survive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-10d5fe05f492cefc74566f590eb23a1a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SAVANNAH&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The savannah is mentioned as a place where early humans faced dangers like lions and hyenas, similar to modern-day situations like dodging taxis in New York."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-10d5fe05f492cefc74566f590eb23a1a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;IVY LEAGUE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Ivy League refers to prestigious universities, where Cannon was a scientist but not confined to academic ivory towers."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-10d5fe05f492cefc74566f590eb23a1a</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 45}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WORLD WAR I&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"World War I is referenced as a context in which Cannon was active, three years into the conflict in 1916."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-10d5fe05f492cefc74566f590eb23a1a</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 45}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LIONS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Lions are mentioned as predators on the savannah, representing a threat to early humans."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-10d5fe05f492cefc74566f590eb23a1a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HYENAS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Hyenas are also mentioned as predators on the savannah, representing another threat to early humans."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-10d5fe05f492cefc74566f590eb23a1a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TAXIS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Taxis are modern vehicles that represent a potential danger or obstacle in urban environments, analogous to predators in the past."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-10d5fe05f492cefc74566f590eb23a1a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TOURISTS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Tourists are individuals who travel to unfamiliar places and may encounter unexpected situations, similar to early humans on the savannah."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-10d5fe05f492cefc74566f590eb23a1a</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 1}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 35}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ELEPHANTS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Elephants are mentioned as potential threats to tourists in modern settings, similar to predators in the past."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-10d5fe05f492cefc74566f590eb23a1a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SCIENTIST-SOLDIER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ROLE"</data>
