  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Sound is produced through the use of vowels, which are the sounds produced by the mouth without obstruction."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-e8e95cffe887226367f1fc5b800af6dc</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VOWELS&quot;" target="&quot;PITCH&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Vowels are influenced by pitch, which refers to the perceived frequency of a sound."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-e8e95cffe887226367f1fc5b800af6dc</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VOWELS&quot;" target="&quot;AMPLIFICATION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Vowels can be amplified through various means, including the use of formants."</data>
