<edge source="&quot;PITCH&quot;" target="&quot;FORMANT&quot;">
  <data key="d4">38.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Formants and pitches must match for clear vowel sounds, especially for sopranos singing high notes."&lt;SEP&gt;"Pitch affects the clarity of vowel sounds produced by singers, especially when the formants and pitches do not match."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-b3c121a5ad657f286818fa5cc9e5c130</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PITCH&quot;" target="&quot;AUDIENCE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The audience's ability to distinguish between certain vowels depends on the match between formants and pitches."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-b3c121a5ad657f286818fa5cc9e5c130</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PITCH&quot;" target="&quot;FIRST FORMANT&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The first formant is particularly important for high-pitched vowels, as seen in the case of sopranos."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-b3c121a5ad657f286818fa5cc9e5c130</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PITCH&quot;" target="&quot;HARMONIC&quot;">
  <data key="d4">35.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Harmonics can align with formants to produce clear vowel sounds, particularly useful for men singing low pitches."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-b3c121a5ad657f286818fa5cc9e5c130</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;FORMANT&quot;" target="&quot;VOWEL&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Formant is crucial for producing clear vowel sounds, especially when the pitch is high, as seen in the case of sopranos."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-b3c121a5ad657f286818fa5cc9e5c130</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;FORMANT&quot;" target="&quot;HARMONIC&quot;">
  <data key="d4">63.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Harmonics can come close to formants to produce clear vowel sounds, particularly useful for men singing low pitches."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-b3c121a5ad657f286818fa5cc9e5c130</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;FORMANT&quot;" target="&quot;SOPRANO&quot;">
  <data key="d4">27.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Sopranos often struggle to produce clear vowel sounds when the fundamental frequency is higher than the first formant of many vowels."&lt;SEP&gt;"Sopranos, who often sing high pitches, may struggle to produce clear vowel sounds due to the lack of a harmonic close to a formant."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-b3c121a5ad657f286818fa5cc9e5c130</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;FORMANT&quot;" target="&quot;AUDIENCE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">32.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Formants and their match with pitches affect how the audience perceives vowel sounds, especially in challenging cases like sopranos."&lt;SEP&gt;"The audience may not be able to distinguish between certain vowels if the formants and pitches do not match, leading to confusion."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-b3c121a5ad657f286818fa5cc9e5c130</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;FORMANT&quot;" target="&quot;MEN&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Men can produce clear vowel sounds when singing low pitches due to the presence of a harmonic close to a formant."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-b3c121a5ad657f286818fa5cc9e5c130</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;FORMANT&quot;" target="&quot;WOMEN&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Women, especially sopranos, may struggle to produce clear vowel sounds when singing high pitches due to the lack of a harmonic close to a formant."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-b3c121a5ad657f286818fa5cc9e5c130</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;FORMANT&quot;" target="&quot;OPERA SINGER&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Opera singers, including sopranos, often face challenges with formant and pitch matching, affecting their performances."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-b3c121a5ad657f286818fa5cc9e5c130</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
